    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Methionyl r-Salmon Oligopeptide-1 sh-Oligopeptide-2 is a single chain recombinant fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from r-Salmon Oligopeptide-1 and sh-Oligopeptide-2 with the code for methionine. The fused peptide contains 85 amino acids and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
